      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2017-04-05</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Child Tax Credit Protection Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to expand the identification requirements for the child tax credit to require taxpayers to provide a valid identification number (i.e., a Social Security account number issued by the Social Security Administration) on their tax returns in addition to the name and taxpayer identification number of each qualifying child. A &quot;valid identification number&quot; does not include a taxpayer identification number issued by the Internal Revenue Service. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <updateDate>2017-04-05T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
